-- French reinsurer Scor posts 35 pct increase in H1 profit
-- By Leigh Thomas
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 01:32AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, July 31 (Reuters) - French reinsurer Scor <SCOR.PA> posted on Thursday a 35.4 percent increase in first-half net profit as its property and casualty business benefited from a low level of major catastrophes.

The company said net profit reached 256 million euros (342.9 million US dollars) in the first half as gross written premiums rose 12.5 percent at constant exchange rates to 5.427 billion euros.